An Act relative to the training, certification, and recognition of constables and civil deputy
sheriffs.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Section 116 of chapter 6 of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2022
2 Official Edition, is hereby amended by inserting after the word “general”, in line 19, the
3 following words:- ; 1 member to be appointed by the Massachusetts Bay Constables Association,
4 Inc.; 1 member to be appointed by the Massachusetts Constables Association, Inc.
5 SECTION 2. Section 1 of chapter 6E of the General Laws, as so appearing, is hereby
6 amended by inserting after the definition of “Officer-involved injury or death” the following
7 definition:-
8 “Other law enforcement officer”, any officer whose statutory or common law authority
9 includes enforcement of civil, criminal, administrative or judicial orders and who does not meet
10 the definition of law enforcement officer, including, but not limited to, civil deputy sheriffs,
11 constables, court officers, harbormasters, parole officers, probation officers, corrections officers;
12 provided, however, that such individual has completed training and in-service education as
1 of 4

13 determined by the commission and the Massachusetts Police Training Committee; provided
14 further, for the purposes of this chapter, “other law enforcement officer” shall include any officer
15 of an elected or appointed constable, whether operating individually or under a legal association
16 or corporation.
17 SECTION 3. Section 4 of said chapter 6E, as so appearing, is hereby amended by adding
18 the following subsection:-
19 (k) The commission shall develop flexible training options for other law enforcement
20 officers not defined as full-time police officers, including part-time, weekend or evening formats.
21 Said training programs shall be sufficient to meet statutory 15and regulatory certification
22 standards and shall require not less than 40 hours of in-service training annually.
23 SECTION 4. Said chapter 6E is hereby further amended by inserting after section 4 the
24 following section:-
25 Section 4A. There shall be within the commission a division of certification of other law
26 enforcement officers, which shall oversee the certification, training and oversight of other law
27 enforcement officers as defined in section 1.
28 SECTION 5. Said chapter 6E is hereby further amended by inserting after section 8 the
29 following section:-
30 Section 8A. There shall be within the division of police standards a division of other law
31 enforcement officer standards, which shall promulgate rules, regulations and standards specific
32 to officers certified under section 4A.
2 of 4

33 SECTION 6. Chapter 29 of the General Laws is hereby amended by inserting after
34 section 2LLLLLL the following section:-
35 SECTION 2MMMMMM. There shall be established and set up on the books of the
36 commonwealth a special revenue fund known as the Civil Deputy Sheriffs and Constables
37 Training Fund to be administered by the secretary of public safety and security. The fund shall
38 receive all revenue from the surcharge established under section 4C 1/2 of chapter 262.
39 Revenues shall be dedicated to the training and certification of other law enforcement officers
40 pursuant to section 4A of chapter 6E.
41 SECTION 7. Chapter 262 of the General Laws is hereby amended by inserting after
42 section 4C the following section:-
43 Section 4C 1/2. Any party entering a complaint, petition or other civil action in any court
44 of the commonwealth in which an initial filing fee is payable shall pay to the clerk of said court a
45 surcharge of $2 in addition to the fee otherwise required by this chapter. All surcharges collected
46 pursuant to this section shall be deposited into the Civil Deputy Sheriffs and Constables Training
47 Fund established under section 2MMMMMM of chapter 29.
48 SECTION 8. The Massachusetts peace officer standards and training commission and the
49 municipal police training committee shall jointly establish curricula specific to the statutory
50 roles, functions and enforcement authority of each category of officer as defined in section 1 of
51 chapter 6E of the General Laws. The curricula shall be developed by a committee that consists of
52 8 persons appointed by the governor from a list of not less than 4 nominees provided by the
53 Massachusetts Bay Constables Association and not less than 4 nominees provided by the
54 Massachusetts Constables Association. Members of the commission shall be professionals from
3 of 4

55 institutions of higher education, the judiciary, the Massachusetts Bar, and recognized subject
56 matter experts with demonstrated experience and knowledge in the relevant field. The curricula
57 shall be modeled after the model used for harbormasters under 515 CMR 16.00. The
58 Massachusetts peace officer standards and training commission shall promulgate regulations not
59 later than 6 months after the effective date of this act where applicable to codify the curricula.
60 SECTION 9. Notwithstanding any general or special law to the contrary, any civil deputy
61 sheriff or constable who has served by election or appointment for not less than 10 consecutive
62 years prior to December 31, 2020, shall be exempt from the certification requirements of chapter
63 6E of the General Laws.
